---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base title="About · Quenchworks" description="Why QuenchWorks exists: a free, independent catalog of hardened, 0-CVE container images and Helm charts.">
  <Header />
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-16">
    <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-ash">About</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">Free hardening, kept independent</h1>

    <div class="mt-6 space-y-5 leading-relaxed text-ash">
      <p>
        For years, teams leaned on a free catalog of community images and charts for the databases,
        caches, and brokers they run every day. When the hardened, low-CVE builds moved behind a paid
        tier and the free catalog was set aside, a lot of that ground was lost.
      </p>
      <p>
        QuenchWorks rebuilds that ground in the open. It is a catalog of the same kinds of datastores,
        each compiled from source on Wolfi into a small nonroot image, scanned to zero fixable CVEs,
        signed, and pinned by digest. Everything is free to use and free to verify.
      </p>
      <p>
        It is also deliberately independent. The charts are written from each project's own upstream
        documentation, not adapted from any other vendor, and the images carry our own artwork, not
        anyone else's trademarks. The point is a clean, honest supply chain you can check yourself.
      </p>
    </div>

    <section class="mt-12 rounded-2xl border border-line bg-graphite p-6 sm:p-8">
      <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-ash">Maintainer</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Mohammad Abu Mattar</h2>
      <p class="mt-2 leading-relaxed text-ash">
        Cloud and DevOps Manager at Motory, with around eight years across full-stack, backend, and
        platform engineering. Day to day that is multi-cloud Kubernetes on AWS, Huawei Cloud, and
        Hetzner, infrastructure as code with Terraform, and CI/CD on Jenkins and ArgoCD. QuenchWorks
        brings that same hardening habit to a free, open catalog.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-5 flex flex-wrap gap-2 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest">
        <a href="https://mkabumattar.com/" class="rounded-lg border border-paper/40 px-3.5 py-2 text-paper transition-colors hover:bg-ink">mkabumattar.com</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/MKAbuMattar" class="rounded-lg border border-line px-3.5 py-2 text-paper transition-colors hover:bg-ink">GitHub</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/quenchworks" class="rounded-lg border border-line px-3.5 py-2 text-ash transition-colors hover:text-paper">QuenchWorks org</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-6 rounded-2xl border border-line bg-graphite px-6 py-8 text-center">
      <p class="text-ash">
        Want a datastore prioritized?{' '}
        <a href="mailto:info@quench-works.com?subject=App%20request" class="font-medium text-paper underline-offset-4 hover:underline">Request an app</a>{' '}
        or browse the{' '}
        <a href="/roadmap" class="font-medium text-paper underline-offset-4 hover:underline">roadmap</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Base>
